H0.text: A warm air mass is the type of air that a cold front is formed when a cold air mass runs into.

H1.text: A hurricane is what a cold front is formed when a cold air mass runs into.

H2.text: Cool air mass is the type of air mass that a cold air mass runs into to form a cold front.

H3.text: Dry air mass is what a cold front is formed when a cold air mass runs into.

A4.text: Cold Front: transition zone from warm air to cold air
